      • setAgentStartArgs

        public def setAgentStartArgs(args : String[]) : void 
        Description copied from class: BootConfig
        Change the arguments to pass to an agent when it is started.

        The agent start arguments constitute a subset of the command line arguments that are replied by BootConfig.getCommandLineArgs(). The arguments that are passed to an agent when it is started are replied by BootConfig.getAgentStartArgs() and changed by BootConfig.setAgentStartArgs(String[]).

        Parameters:
        args - the command line arguments.
